HEADWORD: Petersham
<hw>Pe"ter*sham</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"t⟦etil⟧r*sh⟦acr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Named after Lord <etsep>Petersham</etsep>.]</ety> <def>A rough,
knotted woolen cloth, used chiefly for men's overcoats; also, a coat of
that material.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

